            <title>[AMQ-5967] Temporary disk usage check doesn&apos;t take into account what its already  using</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-5967</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The temporary usage disk check doesn&apos;t take into account what it is already using.  This is fine for the normal case of checking on start up since temporary storage will be empty.  However, with the addition of the new disk limit check task introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-5393&quot; title=&quot;Update disk based limits periodically&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AMQ-5393&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AMQ-5393&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; , this causes a bug as we need to take into account the used space already in the temp store when recomputing this value.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
